<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-12T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-12T17:00:00-05:00" n="245" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d245">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 657.119/229</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SAG1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Schmedeman</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-12T17:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">January 12, 1918—5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>206. Your No. 453, January 9, 2 p.m. Department and War Trade Board
                                will give careful consideration to your suggestions and advise you
                                shortly concerning the publication of our proposal in proper form
                                because we feel that our proposal is fair and reasonable and we
                                think Norwegian people should have full knowledge of our position.
                                For the time being you should defer compliance with Department’s
                                instruction No. 202 of January 5.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PFL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>